South Africa has recorded 4 209 new coronavirus infections in the last 24-hour cycle, taking the total number to 1 704 058. The country has also recorded 120 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Monday. This brings the total number of deaths to 57 183. Recoveries now stand at 1 587 015, representing a recovery rate of 93,0%. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 11 932 018. As DG of HealthI wish to reassure the nation that we remain committed and capable of managing the #COVID19 pandemic; executing a ramped up vaccination programme and running the national programmes as we are led by the Acting Minister of Health, Hon. Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane. pic.twitter.com/hAPD6YfUIq — Department of Health (@HealthZA) June 8, 2021  08 June 2021 #COVID19 statistics in South Africa #CoronavirusSA pic.twitter.com/i0cA7z1g0c — Department of Health (@HealthZA) June 8, 2021 